<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-412-002  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 412 002.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  July 3 1989 v11 n27 p37(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM's research division at work on diverse projects.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Darrow, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scientists at IBM's Research Div involve themselves in projectsfrom the most esoteric science to the most applied technology.andO;For example, one scientist simulates epileptic seizures on aneural network, while a colleague develops an expert system thatcan harmonize Bach cantatas.andP;  Personal initiative is encouraged atthe division, although resources are not unlimited and projectsmust be approved.andP;  There is a dichotomy between technology andscience at the division.andP;  Technological research is driven bymarket considerations, which makes many of the projectscomputer-related, while ideas for scientific projects are judgedby how important they are to science.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. Research Div. (research).andO;Topic:     Research and DevelopmentProject Justification.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>